The paper deals with communication through a channel and proposes a stochastic algorithm for adaptation of the generating distribution of the code. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of feedback and updates to system parameters, which are common in the sub-categories of Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of stochastic algorithms, which is a common topic in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
